<h2>
    <strong>Introduction: Why Hillsboro Is a Great Base for Oregon Anglers</strong>
</h2>
<p>
    Located just west of Portland, <strong>Hillsboro, Oregon</strong> is more than just a tech hub—it’s a gateway to some of the best fishing spots in the Willamette Valley. With urban ponds, clean rivers, and access to major waterways like the Willamette and Columbia Rivers within an hour, Hillsboro is perfect for both casual anglers and die-hard fishermen. Whether you’re after rainbow trout, largemouth bass, or a chance at a seasonal Chinook, the options nearby are endless.
</p>
<h2>
    <strong>Types of Fish You Can Catch Near Hillsboro, Oregon</strong>
</h2>
<p>
    Hillsboro’s proximity to diverse ecosystems offers access to multiple fish species:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Rainbow Trout</strong> – Stocked in urban ponds and rivers.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Largemouth &amp; Smallmouth Bass</strong> – Found in rivers, lakes, and sloughs.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Bluegill and Panfish</strong> – Abundant in small ponds.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Channel Catfish</strong> – Common in the Tualatin River.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Salmon &amp; Steelhead</strong> – Seasonal access via nearby Willamette and Columbia tributaries.
    </li>
</ul>
<h2>
    <strong>Urban and Local Lakes in Hillsboro for Fishing</strong>
</h2>
<h3>
    <strong>Rood Bridge Park Pond</strong>
</h3>
<p>
    A peaceful and scenic park with a small pond stocked with trout. It’s ideal for beginner anglers and families with kids. Try using PowerBait or worms for stocked fish.
</p>
<h3>
    <strong>Bethany Lake</strong>
</h3>
<p>
    Just a short drive north of Hillsboro, this popular pond receives regular trout stockings and supports bass and bluegill populations. It offers ADA-accessible docks and open bank fishing.
</p>
<h3>
    <strong>Commonwealth Lake Park</strong>
</h3>
<p>
    Located in Beaverton, this suburban gem holds bluegill, largemouth bass, and trout. Great for ultralight spin fishing or teaching kids how to fish with a bobber and worm setup.
</p>
<h2>
    <strong>Best Rivers Near Hillsboro for Fishing</strong>
</h2>
<h3>
    <strong>Tualatin River</strong>
</h3>
<p>
    This slow-moving, winding river flows right near Hillsboro. While it’s not known for trout, it’s full of <strong>bass, catfish, crappie</strong>, and the occasional <strong>migrating salmon</strong> during high water years. Great for kayak fishing and backwater sloughs.
</p>
<h3>
    <strong>Willamette River</strong>
</h3>
<p>
    Accessible via nearby cities like <strong>Newberg</strong>, <strong>Wilsonville</strong>, and <strong>St. Paul</strong>, the Willamette offers outstanding fishing for <strong>smallmouth bass</strong>, <strong>spring Chinook salmon</strong>, and <strong>sturgeon</strong>. Use crankbaits or drop-shot rigs near structure.
</p>
